Untested: `register`, `verifyLogin`, `findByUsername`, `listAccounts`, `getActiveAccount`, `setActiveAccount`, `clearActiveAccount`.

Edge cases not covered:
- `register` boundary lengths: displayName exactly 2/24 chars (valid) vs 1/25 (invalid); username exactly 3/20 vs 2/21; password exactly 6 vs 5 chars.
- Duplicate username is case-insensitive (`findByUsername` lowercases) — untested that `"Budi"` collides with `"budi"`.
- `listAccounts` on corrupted JSON or non-array JSON in localStorage — should return `[]`, not throw.
- `listAccounts` filtering out malformed entries (missing fields) via `isAccount`.
- `verifyLogin` with wrong password vs nonexistent username — both must return `null`, not throw.
- `localStorage.setItem` throwing (quota exceeded / disabled storage) — `register` should return `{ ok: false, error: ... }`, not throw.
- Two accounts with usernames differing only by whitespace/case shouldn't both register.

```typescript
// src/game/services/AuthStorageService.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, vi } from 'vitest';
import { AuthStorageService } from './AuthStorageService';

describe('AuthStorageService', () => {
    beforeEach(() => localStorage.clear());

    it('rejects displayName shorter than 2 chars', async () => {
        const r = await AuthStorageService.register('A', 'validuser', 'password1');
        expect(r.ok).toBe(false);
    });

    it('registers and finds account case-insensitively', async () => {
        await AuthStorageService.register('Budi Santoso', 'Budi', 'password1');
        const dup = await AuthStorageService.register('Other', 'budi', 'password2');
        expect(dup.ok).toBe(false);
    });

    it('verifyLogin returns null for wrong password', async () => {
        await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budi', 'password1');
        const result = await AuthStorageService.verifyLogin('budi', 'wrongpass');
        expect(result).toBeNull();
    });

    it('listAccounts returns [] on corrupted storage', () => {
        localStorage.setItem('sikapandawa.accounts', '{not valid json');
        expect(AuthStorageService.listAccounts()).toEqual([]);
    });

    it('listAccounts filters malformed entries', () => {
        localStorage.setItem('sikapandawa.accounts', JSON.stringify([{ id: 'x' }]));
        expect(AuthStorageService.listAccounts()).toEqual([]);
    });

    it('register fails gracefully when localStorage.setItem throws', async () => {
        vi.spyOn(Storage.prototype, 'setItem').mockImplementation(() => { throw new Error('quota'); });
        const r = await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budiuser', 'password1');
        expect(r.ok).toBe(false);
        vi.restoreAllMocks();
    });

    it('setActiveAccount/getActiveAccount/clearActiveAccount round-trip', async () => {
        const r = await AuthStorageService.register('Budi', 'budi', 'password1');
        if (!r.ok) throw new Error('setup failed');
        AuthStorageService.setActiveAccount(r.account.id);
        expect(AuthStorageService.getActiveAccount()?.id).toBe(r.account.id);
        AuthStorageService.clearActiveAccount();
        expect(AuthStorageService.getActiveAccount()).toBeNull();
    });
});
```

Untested: `getProgress`, `saveProgress`, `createInitialProgress`, `totalStars`, `hasSeenIntro`, `markIntroSeen`, `recordLevelResult`, and the private `sanitize`/migration logic.

Edge cases not covered:
- **`sanitize` migration path**: old data without `introSeen` (Progress 02 shape) must migrate to `[]` without dropping `levelStars`/`highestUnlockedLevel`.
- `recordLevelResult` **best-score-never-drops** invariant: recording 1 star after having 3 stars must keep `bestStars === 3` and `isNewBest === false`.
- `recordLevelResult` unlock-never-regresses: if level 2 is already unlocked and player replays level 1 with 1 star, `unlockedLevel` should stay `null` (not re-"unlock" level 2).
- `recordLevelResult` at the last level (`levelId === TOTAL_LEVELS`) must not attempt to unlock level 11.
- `runStars` clamping: negative stars or >3 stars passed in should clamp to `[0,3]`.
- `markIntroSeen` idempotency — calling twice with same `characterId` shouldn't duplicate or double-save.
- `getProgress` on corrupted JSON returns a fresh `initialProgress()`, not a throw.
- `levelStars` values out of range in raw storage (e.g. `-5` or `99`) get clamped by `sanitize`.

```typescript
// src/game/services/ProgressStorageService.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, beforeEach } from 'vitest';
import { ProgressStorageService, TOTAL_LEVELS } from './ProgressStorageService';

describe('ProgressStorageService', () => {
    const ACCOUNT = 'acc-1';
    beforeEach(() => localStorage.clear());

    it('migrates legacy data without introSeen', () => {
        localStorage.setItem(`sikapandawa.progress.${ACCOUNT}`, JSON.stringify({
            highestUnlockedLevel: 2, levelStars: { 1: 3 }
        }));
        const progress = ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT);
        expect(progress.introSeen).toEqual([]);
        expect(progress.levelStars[1]).toBe(3);
        expect(progress.highestUnlockedLevel).toBe(2);
    });

    it('best score never drops', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 3);
        const second = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 1);
        expect(second.bestStars).toBe(3);
        expect(second.isNewBest).toBe(false);
    });

    it('unlock does not regress on replay', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 1); // unlocks level 2
        const replay = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 2);
        expect(replay.unlockedLevel).toBeNull();
    });

    it('does not unlock beyond TOTAL_LEVELS', () => {
        const result = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, TOTAL_LEVELS, 3);
        expect(result.unlockedLevel).toBeNull();
    });

    it('clamps out-of-range runStars', () => {
        const result = ProgressStorageService.recordLevelResult(ACCOUNT, 1, 99);
        expect(result.bestStars).toBe(3);
    });

    it('markIntroSeen is idempotent', () => {
        ProgressStorageService.markIntroSeen(ACCOUNT, 'yudhistira');
        ProgressStorageService.markIntroSeen(ACCOUNT, 'yudhistira');
        const progress = ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT);
        expect(progress.introSeen).toEqual(['yudhistira']);
    });

    it('getProgress returns initial progress on corrupted JSON', () => {
        localStorage.setItem(`sikapandawa.progress.${ACCOUNT}`, '{bad json');
        const progress = ProgressStorageService.getProgress(ACCOUNT);
        expect(progress.highestUnlockedLevel).toBe(1);
        expect(ProgressStorageService.totalStars(progress)).toBe(0);
    });
});
```

