These are tightly coupled to `Phaser.Scene`, so full integration tests need a real `Phaser.Game`; but the **state machines** inside them (open/close, index tracking, debounce) can be unit tested against a lightweight stub instead of mocking all of Phaser.

```typescript
// src/game/ui/__testutils__/sceneStub.ts
export function makeSceneStub() {
    const created: any[] = [];
    const gameObj = () => {
        const obj: any = {};
        ['setDepth','setOrigin','setInteractive','setDisplaySize','setTint','clearTint',
         'setScale','setAlpha','setFillStyle','setStrokeStyle','setVisible','setTexture',
         'setLineSpacing','disableInteractive'].forEach(m => { obj[m] = () => obj; });
        obj.on = () => obj;
        obj.destroy = () => {};
        created.push(obj);
        return obj;
    };
    return {
        objects: created,
        textures: { exists: () => false },
        add: {
            image: () => gameObj(), rectangle: () => gameObj(),
            graphics: () => gameObj(), text: () => gameObj(), dom: () => gameObj()
        },
        events: { once: () => {} },
        time: { delayedCall: (_ms: number, cb: () => void) => cb() }
    } as any;
}
```

- Calling `show()` twice while already open must be a no-op (second call ignored, `visible` guard).
- `hide()` when not open must be a no-op (no crash from destroying empty `objects`).
- `onClose` callback fires exactly once on `hide()`, and is cleared afterward (calling `hide()` again doesn't refire it).

```typescript
// src/game/ui/MessageModal.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
import { MessageModal } from './MessageModal';
import { makeSceneStub } from './__testutils__/sceneStub';

describe('MessageModal', () => {
    it('ignores a second show() call while open', () => {
        const modal = new MessageModal(makeSceneStub());
        modal.show('first');
        modal.show('second'); // should be no-op
        expect(modal.isOpen).toBe(true);
    });

    it('hide() when not open is a no-op', () => {
        const modal = new MessageModal(makeSceneStub());
        expect(() => modal.hide()).not.toThrow();
    });

    it('fires onClose exactly once', () => {
        const onClose = vi.fn();
        const modal = new MessageModal(makeSceneStub());
        modal.show('msg', onClose);
        modal.hide();
        modal.hide(); // already closed
        expect(onClose).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
    });
});
```

- `showLines([], onDone)` with an **empty array** must call `onDone()` immediately without opening the panel.
- `advance()` when not open must be a no-op.
- Last line advance triggers `close()` then `onDone()`, and `isOpen` is `false` afterward.
- Missing speaker key in `speakers` map (falls back to `texture = ''`, uses `__WHITE` fallback) shouldn't throw.
- Calling `showLines` again while one is already showing should reset (`close()` is called first) rather than appending.

```typescript
// src/game/ui/DialogBox.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
import { DialogBox } from './DialogBox';
import { makeSceneStub } from './__testutils__/sceneStub';

describe('DialogBox', () => {
    it('calls onDone immediately for empty lines, without opening', () => {
        const box = new DialogBox(makeSceneStub(), {});
        const onDone = vi.fn();
        box.showLines([], onDone);
        expect(onDone).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
        expect(box.isOpen).toBe(false);
    });

    it('advance() on unopened box is a no-op', () => {
        const box = new DialogBox(makeSceneStub(), {});
        expect(() => box.advance()).not.toThrow();
    });

    it('advances through lines and closes after the last one', () => {
        const box = new DialogBox(makeSceneStub(), {});
        const onDone = vi.fn();
        box.showLines([{ speaker: 'a', text: '1' }, { speaker: 'a', text: '2' }], onDone);
        expect(box.isOpen).toBe(true);
        box.advance();
        expect(box.isOpen).toBe(true);
        box.advance();
        expect(box.isOpen).toBe(false);
        expect(onDone).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
    });

    it('handles an unknown speaker without throwing', () => {
        const box = new DialogBox(makeSceneStub(), {});
        expect(() => box.showLines([{ speaker: 'unknown', text: 'hi' }], () => {})).not.toThrow();
    });
});
```

- `show()` called while already open must `close()` the previous panel first (no leaked objects) — verify `objects` array doesn't grow unbounded across repeated `show()` calls.
- Selecting a choice after `close()` was already called (stale click callback) should not invoke `onSelect` — guarded by `if (!this.open) return;`, but untested.

```typescript
// src/game/ui/ChoicePanel.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
import { ChoicePanel } from './ChoicePanel';
import { makeSceneStub } from './__testutils__/sceneStub';

describe('ChoicePanel', () => {
    it('closing before selection prevents onSelect from firing', () => {
        const panel = new ChoicePanel(makeSceneStub());
        const onSelect = vi.fn();
        panel.show('level1', [{ id: 'A', text: 'x' }], onSelect);
        panel.close();
        expect(panel.isOpen).toBe(false);
        // simulate a stale click event that already fired before close propagated
        expect(onSelect).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
    });

    it('show() while already open replaces prior content', () => {
        const panel = new ChoicePanel(makeSceneStub());
        panel.show('level1', [{ id: 'A', text: 'x' }], () => {});
        expect(() => panel.show('level1', [{ id: 'B', text: 'y' }], () => {})).not.toThrow();
        expect(panel.isOpen).toBe(true);
    });
});
```

- Click-lock debounce: rapid double `pointerup` within 350ms must invoke `onClick` only once.
- `setEnabled(false)` then a `pointerup` must not fire `onClick`.

